      "message": "After looking at this again, this case isn\u0027t quite right. It\u0027s possible for the geometry processor to output a different color than the paint color (a simple example is if the primitive being drawn has per-primitive color, like drawVertices). In that case, the geometry processor will emit some fragment shader code that sets the initial color (per fragment) to the interpolated vertex color.\n\nSo here, I think we need a really simple FP that actually returns the \"input\" color. I don\u0027t think we have anything that does that yet, because almost a no-op. You could base it on GrPremulInputFragmentProcessor.fp, but without the premul (so the .fp main is literally just sk_OutColor \u003d sk_InColor).",
